      "writtenOn": "2026-04-13T23:09:39Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "See my comments in the constructor. I think we should not have a pretend starting \"de-glitched\" value for the GPIO. We should not successfully return a value until we\u0027ve read the GPIO enough times to be valid.\n\nYou could change the return type of the get method to be std::optional\u003cint\u003e. Then the method could return undefined if:\n* This is the first read, so we have no previous read to compare against.\n* We have not seen two reads in a row that matched, so we still don\u0027t know what the value is.\n\nFor initial startup, another option would be to do N reads in a row, perhaps with a very short sleep in between. That would give you a previous reading or two right away. However, if they don\u0027t agree it is still unclear what to return. It could throw an exception I suppose, since that is an error situation.",
